        <fn id="d78e979a1310">
            <label>60</label>
          
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d78e986" publication-type="other">
Solzhenitsyn is certainly aware of the presence of defensists in the ranks of the radicals,
and they may well appear in October 1916. He has also told Western correspondents that he
Intends in that volume to take into consideration "the history of social and intellectual currents
from the end of the 19th century, for they imprinted themselves on the characters." The result
should be a fuller portrait of the pre-revolutionary intelligentsia. (Labedz, Solzhenitsyn, pp.
291 and 276.)</mixed-citation>
            </p>
